Drehbuchautor*in f√ºr Writers Room gesucht (remote)!

Die Sketch-Comedy-Serie ‚ÄûCall Me Barista" folgt der neuen Mitarbeiterin Mia, die in einem hippen Berliner Coffeeshop zwischen Berliner Schnauze, Hipstern und eigenen Selbstzweifeln ihren Platz sucht. Ihre Kollegen schalten um, sobald kein Kunde mehr da ist ‚Äì von cooler Barista-Fassade zu menschlichem Chaos hinter der Theke. Die Serie spielt mit Berliner-Klischees und ehrlichen Momenten und begleitet Mia dabei, wie sie trotz erwarteter Barista-Attitude versucht, sie selbst zu bleiben.

Zur Erweiterung des Writers Rooms, suchen wir kreative K√∂pfe, die Lust haben, in der fr√ºhen Entwicklungsphase einer Sketch-Comedy-Serie dabei zu sein.

Was dich erwartet:

Die M√∂glichkeit, in der fr√ºhen Phase das Konzept im Writers Room mitzuentwickeln (remote)
Die M√∂glichkeit, eigene Sketche und Szenen innerhalb des Konzepts zu entwickeln
Die Freiheit, deinen Fokus selbst zu setzen (z. B. Dialoge, Ideen, Figurenbeschreibungen etc.)

Du:

liebst Comedy, hast kreative Ideen und ein gutes Gef√ºhl f√ºr Timing und Pointen,
bist zuverl√§ssig und arbeitest gerne im Team.

Erfahrung im Writers Room ist nicht zwingend notwendig. Das Projekt ist aktuell noch eigenfinanziert, und somit arbeiten wir alle ohne finanziellen Ausgleich. Bei Auswertung gibt es eine vertraglich geregelte Gewinnbeteiligung, die fair unter allen Mitwirkenden verteilt wird. Geplant ist zun√§chst die Auswertung auf Social-Media-Plattformen. Eine sp√§tere Weiterentwicklung zu einem Sitcom-Serienkonzept ist au√üerdem angedacht. Mehr Informationen findest du auf www.callmebarista.weebly.com

Du willst mitmachen? 
Dann schreib uns: **callmebarista.serie@gmail.com**

Projektbeschreibung:

Du liebst es, im Gr√ºnen zu sein und teilst gerne deine Begeisterung f√ºr Pflanzen, Natur und Garten? Dann suche ich genau dich! F√ºr meinen brandneuen YouTube-Kanal zum Thema Garten, Tipps, Tutorials, neue Ideen und interessantes G√§rtnern suche ich eine motivierte Schauspielerin, die mit Charme, Humor und Leidenschaft das Publikum mit auf eine unterhaltsame gr√ºne Reise nimmt. Gerne auch Anf√§nger und Neueinsteiger im Bereich Schauspiel und oder Garten. Keine Vorkenntnisse erforderlich.

Ich biete eine spannende und kreative Zusammenarbeit in einem wachsenden YouTube-Projekt, bei dem du nicht nur dein schauspielerisches Talent einbringen kannst, sondern auch die M√∂glichkeit hast, die Gartenwelt auf unterhaltsame, interessante und attraktive Weise zu pr√§sentieren.

Was dich erwartet:

Themen: Alles rund um Garten, interessantes G√§rtnern, Tipps f√ºr Anf√§nger, Gartentipps und Anbauversuche, DIY-Projekte, kleine Bauten im Garten und vieles mehr! Keine Vorkenntnisse erforderlich.

Zielgruppe: Eine attraktive Frau zwischen 18 und 35 Jahre jung. Mit Spa√ü an schauspielerischer Darstellung von gew√ºnschten Charakteren und Eigenschaften. Mit Impro-F√§higkeiten bei Text und Darstellung.

Format: Informative, unterhaltsame und begeisternde Videos, in denen du verschiedene Gartenthemen und Projekte vorstellst ‚Äì von Anleitungen und Tutorials √ºber kleine Bauten bis hin zu pers√∂nlichen Erlebnissen im Garten. Keine Vorkenntnisse erforderlich.

Drehort: Au√üenaufnahmen in einem gro√üen Garten in Leverkusen, nahe K√∂ln. Wetterabh√§ngig, gute Koordination von verl√§sslichen Drehzeiten notwendig.

Verantwortung: Du wirst das Gesicht des Kanals und pr√§sentierst die Themen in einer lebendigen und authentischen Art. Du wirst regelm√§√üig vor der Kamera stehen und mit mir zusammenarbeiten, um Inhalte zu erstellen, die sowohl lehrreich, interessant, ansehnlich und unterhaltsam sind.

Was ich von dir erwarte:

Schauspielerisches Talent: Du bist in der Lage, deine Rolle authentisch und mit Begeisterung zu verk√∂rpern, vor der Kamera zu stehen und spontan zu agieren. Text auch sehr gerne improvisierst mit kleinen Stichwortvorgaben.

Interesse an sehr einfacher Gartent√§tigkeit: Ein grundlegendes Interesse an Pflanzen, Gartenarbeit oder gr√ºnem Daumen ist von Vorteil, aber nicht zwingend erforderlich ‚Äì ich freue mich auch √ºber frische Perspektiven und die Bereitschaft den Kanal mitzuentwickeln und gerne eigene Ideen einzubringen!

Positives Auftreten: Du bist ein offener, freundlicher Typ, der gerne im Rampenlicht steht und es versteht, das Publikum zu begeistern. Dich selbstst√§ndig stylen und attraktiv herrichten kannst, um nicht so auszusehen als h√§ttest du deinen Kopf gerade in einen Maulwurfsh√ºgel gesteckt.

Flexibilit√§t: Du bist bereit, an verschiedenen Projekten zu arbeiten ‚Äì von Tutorials √ºber Garten- und technische Tipps bis hin zu kreativen Gartenvideos.

Aufgeschlossen: Keine Angst davor dich neuen Dingen gegen√ºberzustellen. Dich nicht scheust auch mal mit den gesch√ºtzten H√§nden in der Erde zu buddeln oder eine Gie√ükanne zu tragen.

Was ich biete:

Verg√ºtung: Weil der Kanal noch entstehen und wachsen muss, kann ich zu Beginn eine Pauschale von 100 Euro pro Video bieten. Die fertigen Videos sollen zwischen 30 und 50 Minuten lang werden. Daher sch√§tze ich die Drehzeit auf 4 bis 5 Stunden pro Video. Kann auch deutlicher weniger sein wenn alles gut l√§uft.

Langfristige Zusammenarbeit: Die M√∂glichkeit, in einem wachsenden Projekt mitzukommen und langfristig ein Teil einer tollen Unternehmung zu werden.

Kreative Freiheit: Du kannst deine eigene Pers√∂nlichkeit in die Rolle einbringen und mit mir gemeinsam Ideen entwickeln.

Spa√ü und Abwechslung: Arbeiten in einer kreativen, abwechslungsreichen und entspannten Atmosph√§re rund um den neuen Kanal der viele begeistern wird.

Erstellung eigener Fotos oder Videos f√ºr deine Set-Card m√∂glich.

Das Team: Bin zur Zeit nur ich, auf der Suche nach Menschen die Spa√ü daran haben den Kanal gemeinsam zu starten, auszubauen und weit nach vorne zu bringen.

Wie du dich bewerben kannst:

Wenn du glaubst, dass du die perfekte Person f√ºr diese Rolle bist, dann schick mir bitte:

Ein kurzes Vorstellungsvideo (max. 1‚Äì2 Minuten), in dem du dich selbst vorstellst und mir erz√§hlst, warum du dich f√ºr diesen Job interessierst. Zeige mir, wie du vor der Kamera agierst.

Ein kurzes Motivationsschreiben, in dem du kurz erkl√§rst, warum du gerne f√ºr einen Garten-YouTube-Kanal arbeiten m√∂chtest.

Sehr gerne auch ohne Vorerfahrungen im Bereich Schauspiel und oder Garten. Bist du vollst√§ndig neu in diesem Bereich, m√∂chtest dich aber gerne ausprobieren, hast du hier die M√∂glichkeit. Sei offen und melde dich einfach.

Sind noch Fragen offen, dann gerne einfach eine Mail an mich.

Bewerbungsfrist ist der 21.12.2025

Kontakt: gardenbunnys247@gmail.com

Ich freuen mich darauf, von dir zu h√∂ren und gemeinsam in die Welt von YouTube einzutauchen!

Zus√§tzliche Hinweise:

Die Zusammenarbeit erfolgt auf Projektbasis, aber mit Aussicht auf eine langfristige Zusammenarbeit, wenn der Kanal w√§chst.

Alle Bewerbungen nat√ºrlich werden vertraulich behandelt.

If your self-tapes keep blending in‚Ä¶ this class will change that.

Casting directors don‚Äôt just see what you‚Äôre doing,

they see what you‚Äôre feeling.

When the camera moves closer, every flicker of truth (or fakeness) becomes visible.

Tonight at The AWA Lab, we‚Äôll explore how to make that closeness your superpower.

üé• Close-Ups & Extreme Close-Ups: The Art of Subtle Emotion

Learn how to stay grounded, still, and alive, so the lens can‚Äôt look away.

items.text: Come audit this weekly class that takes place right here in Sandy on Monday, Tuesday, or Wednesday nights and take your ability to the next level. Every student performs in front of the class every week. What decides auditions is the quality of the audition tape and what determines the quality of your tape is your Understanding of BEATS and ACTIONS and equally importantly - YOUR ABILITY TO EMOTIONALLY BRING THE GOODS with simplicity and precision. Come sit in on a class to see what it's all about.

Hello, I am looking for collaborators for the making of a Documentary about life: The myth of success. Which will cover the topics of genetics, destiny and all the elements that make a person to become successful or to end up in the streets.

This is an independent project with no remuneration attached to it.

Location: London, UK

Duration: 3-8 weeks

Starting date: 10.12.2025
items.previewDescription: What makes a person successful while for others there's less of it? What is success? If it can be quantified, can it be reproduced? And what are the factors that influence someone's success in life? Interviews with students, people on the street, beggars, specialists (psychologists, psychiatrists, s...
items.title: Documentary Project No.75 : Debunking Success

items.text:
Location: Berlin

Shooting: mid-January

None paid (student project) + food + footage reel

ROLE HELEN (Lead, playing age 23-30)

Helen is the daughter of Hades, living in the mortal world in isolation.

She‚Äôs observant, emotionally detached on the surface, but with a complex inner world.

Her energy is quiet, intense, and unpredictable; she feels outside of humanity while desperately

studying it.

She is not a stereotype ‚Äústrong female lead‚Äù.

She is layered, morally grey, dry, curious, bitter, vulnerable, and intimidating without trying.

A character who barely shows her emotions but feels everything deeply.

This role requires:

‚óè strong subtle acting

‚óè microexpressions

‚óè comfort with psychological + mystical scenes

‚óè ability to play someone who is always scanning her surroundings

‚óè comfort acting opposite horror elements (no gore, more psychological/supernatural)

No previous fantasy experience needed, just strong emotional control and complexity.

All ethnicities welcome.

ABOUT THE PROJECT 

This is a 30-minute TV pilot for my graduation project and a proof-of-concept.

The tone is similar to The Sandman, Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth, and Only Lovers Left Alive; dark, poetic,

mythological, grounded in emotional realism.

The story explores:

‚óè Mythology incorporated into modern Berlin

‚óè Identity and isolation

‚óè Power structures

‚óè Neurodivergent perception

‚óè The horror of being watched by the divine

Helen is the center of this world.

We offer a complex role with depth and high-quality footage for your acting reel. As stated

before, this is a proof-of-concept pilot episode. The goal is to apply for further funding and production support in 2026 and continue the series.

REQUIREMENTS

‚óè Based in Berlin or able to travel.

‚óè Availability for shooting in mid-January.

‚óè Comfortable with night scenes and horror tones.

‚óè Able to commit to rehearsals in December.

TO APPLY!!

Send to: celia.t@catalyst-students.com

‚óè Recent headshot or clear photo.

‚óè Showreel (if available).

‚óè Your age + where you are based.

ANNOUNCEMENT ‚Äî Buckland & Gun arrives in London

Buckland & Gun is proud to announce its expansion into London, led by Founder Nick Buckland.

After 17 successful years operating across Australia  and having established a presence in New Zealand over the past 12 months  the company is now opening its London base as Nick returns to England to further develop opportunities for actors around the world.

This next chapter marks an exciting step in Buckland & Gun‚Äôs ongoing mission:
to support, represent, and elevate diverse, professionally trained actors across global markets.

Further updates will be released in the coming days, including:

Open castings to build the new London talent book

Professional audition workshops

Details of the upcoming booking and enrolment system

Buckland & Gun is delighted to begin this new journey in one of the world‚Äôs great creative capitals.

Welcome to the London chapter.

CASTING CALL

For upcoming Non-Union Series, ANCIENT BODIES SEASON 2.

Looking for Males Of Israeli /Jewish Descent, 20s-40s (NO TATTOOS PLEASE)

Non-Union Only
Rate: $200 per day
Manitoba Residents Only (MUST have SIN #) 
Filming in Winnipeg and the surrounding areas December 11 to 12 and  December 16 to 19. 
Must have full day and evening availability 

Please email info@oafilmstudio.com with the subject line: 
Your Ethnicity- Male 20-40s- YOUR NAME

Send the following info:
- Full Name
- Age
- Gender
- Ethnicity
- Height
- Phone
- Email Address
- State that you are non-union and a Manitoba resident with a SIN# and work permit
- Your availability from December 11-12 and December 16-19 (Must be available all day and evening)
- State if you have tattoos
- Do you have your own transportation or a reliable ride?
- If you have any acting or performance experience, let us know (Speaking, SOC, Background, Theatre, Public speaking, Social Media). No experience is alright.
- 2 Current (TAKEN DAY OF SUBMISSION) Photos (1 selfie & 1 Full Body Shot)

Please share!

#Winnipeg #winnipegcastingcall #WinnipegActing
Onalee Ames Film Studio 
150 Stafford St, Winnipeg, MB

items.text:
Hey everyone, my name is Alix üëã

I moved to Manchester on 3 November 2025 and I‚Äôm still learning my way around Salford and Manchester city centre! I don‚Äôt drive and I don‚Äôt currently have any travel passes, so I‚Äôm looking for opportunities that are walking distance or directly on Metrolink tram routes üöä in:

‚úÖ Manchester city centre
‚úÖ Salford areas (easy to reach by tram)

I‚Äôd really appreciate recommendations that are actually in tram zones or the city centre ‚Äî tram + walking is my only way around right now.

A bit about me & my situation ‚Äî I‚Äôm currently under Salford social services and sadly they‚Äôve made it clear they won‚Äôt provide support, so I‚Äôm living up here with no support at all. My family live down south, I don‚Äôt know anyone here yet, and it‚Äôs been very isolating and lonely‚Ä¶ but I‚Äôm staying proactive and positive üíõ

üé≠ My main passion is theatre and acting

I want to build experience onstage and backstage, especially in:

‚ú® Lighting & stage tech
üé® Set/prop painting
üîß Stagehand / backstage crew / stage tech
üçπ Theatre bar / FOH / front of house / bar work
üé¨ Film & TV set experience in the future

Long-term dream:

üé¨ Acting roles on film/TV sets
üì∫ Something like soap acting (Corrie style!)
üé• TV & movie roles

I‚Äôve tried contacting companies myself with no luck (emails, calls, social media, applications ‚Äî all ignored ‚ùå) but I‚Äôm not giving up.

‚úÖ Availability: 7 days a week, mornings to evenings, any hours

I‚Äôm not here for sympathy ‚Äî I just want someone to say:

üíõ ‚ÄúI‚Äôll give you a chance.‚Äù
üíõ A place to volunteer, learn, and build experience
üíõ Roles near the tram lines / city

Please feel free to:

üì© Message me
üè∑Ô∏è Tag places or people
üí¨ Comment suggestions

Thank you so much for reading ü§ç
Let‚Äôs make Manchester feel like home ü´∂üöäüé≠üêæ

items.text: Proud to share this next chapter  bringing Buckland & Gun home to Great Britain

sharedPost.text:
ANNOUNCEMENT ‚Äî Buckland & Gun arrives in London

Buckland & Gun is proud to announce its expansion into London, led by Founder Nick Buckland.

After 17 successful years operating across Australia  and having established a presence in New Zealand over the past 12 months  the company is now opening its London base as Nick returns to England to further develop opportunities for actors around the world.

This next chapter marks an exciting step in Buckland & Gun‚Äôs ongoing mission:
to support, represent, and elevate diverse, professionally trained actors across global markets.

Further updates will be released in the coming days, including:

Open castings to build the new London talent book

Professional audition workshops

Details of the upcoming booking and enrolment system

Buckland & Gun is delighted to begin this new journey in one of the world‚Äôs great creative capitals.

Welcome to the London chapter.

Buckland and Gun - AU  Buckland and Gun - NZ 
#bucklandandgun #londonactors #casting #ActingOpportunities

media.ocrText: May be a graphic of text that says 'A BUCKLAND & GUN ARRIVES IN LONDON After 17 years championing actors across Australia and recently expanding into New Zealand- Buckland & Gun is opening a new chapter in Loron. Founder Nick Buckland is returning home to England with a simple mission: to open doors for actors around the world and help emerging and established performers find meaningful opportunities across film, television, theatre, commercial work, and voice. We're thrilleo to be here. More soon. BUCKLAND. GUN'

items.text:
Location: Either near Irvine, CA or Ontario, CA
Shoot Dates: December 3, 4, or 5
Time Commitment/Shoot Length: 3-4 Hours 
Compensation: $100 flat for 3‚Äì4 hours + a meals or snacks/drinks 

Project Type: I‚Äôm a sports medicine/orthopedic professional, not a filmmaker, but I‚Äôve been tasked with producing an updated educational video for use in college classrooms. I‚Äôm looking for an outgoing, open-minded, athletic female model/actress (18‚Äì30) to participate in this short film that illustrates the accessibility and mobility challenges someone experiences during a temporary leg injury. All equipment (crutches, splint/cast) is provided. The cast is non-permanent and applied/removed safely.

About the Role:
You‚Äôll portray someone recovering from a short-term lower-limb injury while navigating everyday environments‚Äîstores, stairs, hallways, buildings‚Äîusing crutches and a removable cast/splint. The filming will take place over 3‚Äì4 hours in one day and will be edited to appear as multiple days. You will be responsible for your own makeup/wardrobe but we can discuss what is expected!

Creative Collaboration:
Because I‚Äôm approaching this from a healthcare perspective rather than a filmmaking one, I welcome creative input and collaboration. If you have ideas, insights, or personal experience that could make the scenes more realistic or engaging, I‚Äôm very open to incorporating them.

Who I‚Äôm Looking For:
Female, 18‚Äì30
Athletic, active, or fitness-oriented
Comfortable with walking non weight bearing on crutches
Good on camera and able to portray authentic emotion (pain, irritation, joy, etc.)
Able to bring a few outfit options and personal items (e.g., backpack, different outfits)
Acting/modeling experience not required
Experience with crutches or prior injuries is a plus
Based in Southern California

Project Details
Amateur, non-union
Educational, documentary-style
Mostly improvised with some guidance
Small, supportive, low-pressure environment
Opportunity to contribute creatively

To Apply
Please DM me, comment below, or email brettsmithh316@gmail.com with:
Your name + age
Headshot and full-body photo
A short intro about you addressing relative experience (video recording preferred)
Relevant experience (acting, sports, crutches/cast experience)
Your availability Dec 3, 4, or 5

Thanks!

## **Casting Breakdown: *****OUROBOROS***

A Psychological Horror film. The Fourth Film from Pineal Dreams Productions.

‚ÄúWhen a young couple suffer the pain of a miscarriage; they retreat to a cottage in the woods to try and heal. Unfortunately they quickly discover that you can never run away from your trauma‚Äô

**üéì Lead Roles**

**AMAIA**

**Female | Playing age: 20-30 | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A young woman, grief-stricken, haunted by a recent miscarriage. Intelligent, emotionally complex, volatile, and deeply human. Fluctuates between tender vulnerability and violent dissociation.

 **Performance notes:** Requires a wide emotional range ‚Äî subtle detachment, raw grief, moments of horror, as well as serenity towards the end.  Appears in nearly every scene.

 **Comparable roles:** Charlotte Gainsbourg (*Antichrist*), Essie Davis (*The Babadook*), Jennifer Connelly *(Requiem for a Dream), *Isabelle Adjani *(Possession)*

This is a dual-role as they will also be playing the character of Amaia‚Äôs Doppelganger

**AMAIA'S DOPPELGANGER **

**Female | Same actor as Amaia preferred**

 **Description:** An uncanny mirror of Amaia ‚Äî at times gentle, at times mocking or malevolent. Not a "villain" but an emotional specter. She represents Amaia‚Äôs true opinion of herself, and pulls at her mental fragility to attempt to make her finally give in to her pain.

 **Performance notes:** If dual casting is not possible, physical resemblance and matched acting style are key. The role is symbolic and dreamlike.

 **Type:** Similar movement to Amaia, but with a more ‚Äòfloaty‚Äô and ethereal feel to it.

The nature of a dual role would suit an actress who really wants a challenge - as well as the maximum amount of screen time for any character in the film. Hopefully, a brilliant showcase role for talent who want to establish themselves as a critically respected performer, as they will be carrying the vast bulk of the film‚Äôs emotional core.

We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with three scenes needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require ten days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**DONN**

**Male | Playing age: 30-40 | Ethnicity: Open**

**Description:** Amaia‚Äôs partner. Kind, supportive, but emotionally shut down. A man attempting to cope through suppression - a misguided attempt at stoicism as he believes she must be strong to support Amaia - whose quiet unraveling becomes key to the resolution.

 **Performance notes:** Understated emotionality. Requires physical performance (injury, crawling, etc.) and strong presence in silence.

 **Comparable roles:** Michael Fassbender (*Shame*), Mads Mikkelsen (*Another Round*), Javier Bardem *(Mother!)*, Harry Dean Stanton *(Paris, Texas)*

Filming block will be the same as Amaia‚Äôs. Five-day block (Hopefully), as well as shoots at just three other locations.Ten days of filming maximum, but this could always change if re-shoots are necessary, and one day of ADR work will be required.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

PAID - A minimal fee. Which can be discussed upon application. This is our fourth short-film, and the first we‚Äôve offered payment for. It was a late decision, as we appreciate experience doesn‚Äôt pay the rent. However, being a tiny, self-funded studio, it is a relatively small amount.

All food and transport - and accommodation, if needed - also covered.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

**üë• Supporting Roles -**

**THE UMBRA**

**Male | Playing age: ANY | Tall, slender, distinctive presence | Ethnicity: Open**

 **Description:** A silent manifestation of trauma that watches over and manipulates events ‚Äî a mythic observer of Amaia‚Äôs trauma. Symbol of death, memory, or fate.

 **Performance notes:** No dialogue for a vast majority of the script, though requires a sequence of some very carnival-esque dialogue. Face never seen. Must convey gravitas, mystery, and quiet threat through stillness and gaze.

 **Type:** Dancer, mime, or physical performer backgrounds welcomed. Could even opt for the possibility of a physical performer, and a separate voice-actor. So any voice-actors interested, please feel free to contact us.

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

topComments.text: Messaged you on Insta! I think it might have gone to your message requests :)

Similar Roles: Doug Jones (Pan‚Äôs Labyrinth), Tim Purcell (The Babadook), Javier Botet (Slenderman)

The Umbra appears in the Cottage and scenes surrounding it, all of which will be filmed during the scheduled five-day filming block.

There will also be one additional day, in which you will be required for a single scene that takes place in a different location.

Re-shoots are of course always possible, and will be needed for one ADR session for dialogue provided during an animated sequence.

PAID - But a smaller fee than Amaia/Donn as will be required for less days.  This can be discussed upon application. We aim to film a bulk of the filming in one five-day block, with one scene needing filming elsewhere. We anticipate filming will require tsix days, with one day of ADR needed for additional dialogue/audio fixes.

We know it‚Äôs frustrating when actors dangle around for months between shoots, so will be aiming to avoid that. We anticipate all filming to be completed in a 2 month period.

The film cannot be released by us until payment has been completed. That‚Äôs our promise to you.

We are a very small studio, and this is our fourth short. However, our mantra has always been a ‚Äòquality over quantity‚Äô approach. We take great pride in not just making a film, but really thinking it through on a technical level. We appreciate classic and arthouse cinema, and are far more interested in making a good film than red carpet events.

Our three shorts so far have been screened at over 20 festivals, picking up around 14 awards - including two IMDB qualified awards. (best actor for Jackson Wright in Inside The Abyss). Our latest film has seen our lead - Tash Morley - pick up three awards. We aim for this to be our best film yet.

If interested in the roles, please contact me directly via the Pineal Dreams Instagram page. My own personal profiles - both Joshua Moulini√© (Facebook/Instagram). Or Email me directly on [Moulinie23@gmail.com](mailto:Moulinie23@gmail.com)

We hope to hear from you all very soon!

A tense, atmospheric psychological short film set in Czechoslovakia, following a young woman haunted by visions of an imposing KGB spy as she searches for the truth behind her past.

üé≠ **ZUZANNA**
*Female Presenting | 18‚Äì25*

*Male Presenting | 40s‚Äì50s*
Worn down by years under an oppressive regime. Emotionally numb but deeply devoted to giving his daughter the freedom he never had.

9 Jahre ist es her, nun ermitteln Judy Hopps und Nick Wilde erneut  in ZOOMANIA 2 (Stadtkinocenter Laa,  Babylon Kino Horn und Filmb√ºhne Waidhofen/Ybbs).

Den Alltag eines Ehepaares nach vielen gemeinsamen Beziehungsjahren bringt uns Neele Leana Vollmar empathisch auf die Leinwand. So nebenbei durften wir auch mit der Regisseurin ein paar Worte wechseln.

Ausserdem gibt es noch eine Doppelconferance im Interview mit Cynthia Erivo und Ariana Grande sowie erz√§hlt uns Rick Kavanian √ºber die Arbeit als Synchronsprecher zum neuesten Disney Zeichentrick Blockbuster.

Weitere Filmtipps wie zb aus dem Kronenkino Mistelbach und Musik aus 80 Jahren Moviehistory pr√§sentiert Ihnen Sarah Fuchs. 

Mittwoch 26.11.25 von 18 bis 19h auf radioYpsilon 94.5 oder via Stream (http://mp3.radioypsilon.at:8000/)

CASTING CALL FOR STUDENT SHORT FILM (PAID) - AIRTIME 

Hi, we are students at Nottingham Trent University making a short film about a local live news broadcast minutes away from air where everything just keeps going wrong. The entire film will take place in one shot, or at least have the appearance it is.

üìÖProduction date: January 2026

üìçLocation: Nottingham

üí∞Pay: Paid opportunity

üé•Production company: Nottingham Trent University (Student project)

ROLES AVAILABLE

üé≠Character: Martin - The director of the morning news broadcast in *Airtime*. A crass man whose declining home life has driven him to becoming a functioning alcoholic whose grip on his own life is slipping, which is starting to affect his professional life as his apathy grows. Despite his plethora of problems, he can be an amicable personality in the right circumstances and is a skilled communicator and leader. Personality wise, he combines the jadedness of adulthood with a childlike disconnect between his actions/attitude and its effects on himself and other people around him.

üë§Age Range: 35 - 50

üéØType: Male Actor

üåçEthnicity: White British

üìåBased in or able to work in Nottingham, UK

üé≠Character: Bethany - The assistant director in the morning news program in *Airtime*. She is highly professional and level-headed, oftentimes having to go beyond the call of duty due to the incompetence or indifference of the people around her. Bethany is very patient and would rather move the production along and work hard than waste time arguing with Martin or other members of the crew not pulling their weight. Despite her forbearance, she is finding it more difficult to bite her tongue as time goes on.

üë§Age Range: 20 - 30

üéØType: Female Actor

üåçEthnicity: Open

üìåBased in or able to work in Nottingham, UK

If anyone is interested or wants more information please DM me. 

Alternatively email me, [isaacoharefilm@gmail.com](mailto:isaacoharefilm@gmail.com)

Please include your age, headshot, and role you are applying for. We can‚Äôt wait to hear from you soon!

**CASTING CALL FOR A 10-MIN SHORT FILM**
Hi everyone! We‚Äôre seeking local actors for a neorealist short film shooting in late January in Vancouver. The film is intended for 2026 festival submissions.

**Logline:**

A college student volunteers on a visual-assist app to help an elderly man in his small apartment, unaware that a quiet glitch has turned their private calls into a public stream.

**Production Details**

‚Ä¢ Location: Vancouver, BC

‚Ä¢ Shoot Window: Late January ‚Äì Early February 2026 (TBD)

‚Ä¢ Genre: Neorealist Drama

‚Ä¢ Non-Union / Volunteer

‚Ä¢ Meals + IMDb credit provided

**ROLES**

**MAYA ‚Äî Female, 19‚Äì24 (Open Ethnicity)**

Quiet, inward, emotionally guarded.
Minimal dialogue; performance driven by micro-reactions and natural handheld close-ups.
Must be comfortable with subtle, restrained acting.
Grounded student under stress ‚Äî *Wendy & Lucy*, *Never Rarely Sometimes Always* tone.

**LEON ‚Äî Male, 65‚Äì80 (Open Ethnicity)**

Soft-spoken, solitary, dignified.
Partially visually impaired; actor need not be visually impaired but must portray limited vision naturally.
Understated physicality: small gestures, hesitation, lived-in presence.

**TO APPLY**

Please send the following to **seetogetherfilm@gmail.com**
Subject: **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì MAYA‚Äù** or **‚ÄúSEE TOGETHER ‚Äì LEON‚Äù**
‚Ä¢ Recent headshot
‚Ä¢ Short introduction (video or written)
‚Ä¢ Availability (Jan‚ÄìFeb 2026)
‚Ä¢ Any naturalistic acting samples (if available)

We will cast people first through self-tapes.

Thank you!

items.text:
LOGLINE: 

In a distant future, Callie Jones works as a hacker whose illegal activities draw the attention of the future's police force, potentially endangering their budding romance and their freedom.

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

Faye (she/her, trans-femme, 25-30) - Faye is an aspiring fashion designer and a close friend/ love interest to Callie. She is a gentle person who has plenty of love for anyone she meets, though even her patience has its limits. Years of living paycheque to paycheque in an unforgiving capitalist dystopia have her yearning for a stable life where she can be free to create and to love freely.

Shooting dates: Dec 1st, 2nd, 13th, 14th

Non union, paid work ($100 per day, open to negotiation), lunch provided.

Please send a headshot, resume, and demo reel (if applicable) to iamkarlyelyse@gmail.com

sharedPost.text:
Artist:  Benedictus quasi Deus
Album: Out of the dark (Falco Cover))(Single)
Label: Eigenlabel
Release: 21.10.2025

Benedictus quasi Deus' Interpretation von ‚ÄûOut of the dark‚Äú, das ein Falco Cover ist, ist recht ansprechend konzipiert, aber bisher nur als Youtube-Video verf√ºgbar. Der Musiker beginnt mit sanften Panfl√∂tent√∂nen und sein Gesang kommt anfangs sehr leise her√ºber. Dieses verst√§rkt die sehr innige Haltung. Sp√§ter werden die Vocals rauer. Man kann also von einem Break sprechen. Energetische Effekte bringen einen besonderen und starken Touch hinein. 

Ein starker Bass verleiht dem Song einen rockigen Flair und das vorliegende Cover ist sehr interessant aufgebaut. Falcos Grundmelodie ist zu erkennen und Benedictus quasi Deus verfremdet das Original, so dass ich es als eine sehr gute Interpretation bezeichnen kann.  

Positiv herauszustellen ist auch in der Videodarstellung der Gebrauch von einer Kerze, Explosionen und Feuer, die ein dynamisches Ambiente hervorrufen.

Youtube-Video: https://youtu.be/gfvWL6h4GKk?si=YR5U2x_QCoWfQUfy

Roman Golub 
Northern Art Music - Bodystyler Musikmagazin

items.text:
Filmmakers! You're invited to our transformative meetup at Empowering Filmmakers! 

Every Saturday from 4-6pm in Los Angeles.

Join a vibrant community of aspiring filmmakers who are passionate about storytelling through narrative films. We aim to support one another in bringing our collective visions to life and creating movies together. By collaborating across different departments, we can harness each other's strengths and creativity. We all invest our energy and passion into each other‚Äôs projects and turn our individual ideas into a vibrant reality.

Our meetups foster creativity and connection, allowing you to collaborate with like-minded individuals. Whether you're a writer, actor, director, producer, or cinematographer, you will find support in honing your craft. Please note that we focus exclusively on narrative films.

Membership is FREE!.

Complete this form if you'd like to become a member.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScJPx3EyAE9HyemwIwzT-Q67ENY10I_nnWcbRZALch2wEo95w/viewform?usp=header

Alle, die mitmachen, werden nat√ºrlich **im Abspann genannt**.

Wir suchen **kurzfristig Komparsen** f√ºr mehrere Szenen in Berlin:

**üîπ DONNERSTAG, 04.12 ‚Äì Clubszene**

üìç **Maaya Club Berlin**
üïí **11:30 ‚Äì 13:30 Uhr**

CASTING CALL ‚Äì Independent Short Film (LONDON)

We are casting for an upcoming student short film exploring obsession, ambition, and the dark side of the ballet world.

Production: Student film via The American University of Rome

Director: Maxine Sutton

Cinematographer: Georgia Blackson

Shooting Dates: December 12‚Äì19

ROLES

NATASHA (Lead)

Female, 18‚Äì28

Ballet-trained (advanced preferred)

Must convey vulnerability, intensity, and psychological depth

Strong acting, presence, and physical performance required

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

RUDOLPH

Male, 25‚Äì40

Dance experience preferred

Embodies both beauty and cruelty ‚Äî a man who inspires awe, fear, and complete submission.

Slavic accent preferred.

Pay: 250‚Ç¨ flat rate for entire production

SYNOPSIS

Natasha, a talented but tormented ballerina, navigates a high-stakes audition that tests the limits of her physical and psychological endurance. As she strives for perfection under the watchful eye of the enigmatic Rudolph, the line between reality and terror begins to blur, forcing her to confront the true cost of ambition.

TO APPLY

Please complete the audition form and send it, along with a headshot, to: maxineclairesutton@gmail.com

Please note: Do not friend request me as I do not add anyone who I do not know irl. I will not be answering anyone who friend requests me. Please comment below.

In addition to my other project, I am looking for a video/sound editor for a short 5 minute film about a young couple going through infertility. 

The candidate does not have to be local to me, just needs to be U.S. based, have availability in January to work on this with me, and be an excellent and prompt communicator.

I have all of the footage and time stamps with descriptions. 

My budget is small, about $400, as this was a student project. 

I have a complete version that was edited by someone who did not capture my vision and could not fix issues that needed correcting. That version is available to be utilized and corrected. The main issue that needs the most attention is the sound as there is a lot of wind within some of the footage, otherwise it will need basic color grading and rearranging the order of some the footage.

I am looking to have this complete by early February 2026 in order to keep up with film festival circuits for next year.

If this sounds like something that is doable to you and would be of interest to you, please comment below.

topComments.text: Just create your own.  Even if you get roles you will have to wait until they come out.
I‚Äôd self tape some monologues and if able find local actors in the same boat who need footage and work together on a quick short film.

Ready for the best summer of your life? Join our Entertainment Teams and work under the sun in beautiful Greece. ‚òÄÔ∏èüá¨üá∑

WE ARE LOOKING FOR PERFORMERS:

Position: (Aerialist, Acrobat, Juggler ‚Äì performing shows at various hotels)
Contract Period: 1 May ‚Äì 31 October 2026
Monthly Net Salary: From ‚Ç¨1,000 - 1500‚Ç¨ (depending on experience, skills, and performance)
Employment Type: Swiss contract or self-employed freelancer

Venues: 4‚òÖ and 5‚òÖ hotels located on Kos, Crete, or Rhodes Island, Greece

Terms and Benefits
 ‚Ä¢ 1‚Äì2 weeks of free rehearsals prior to the contract start date, depending on the candidate‚Äôs progress in learning choreography
 ‚Ä¢ One day off per week
 ‚Ä¢ 1‚Äì2 performances per day( 1hour show )
 ‚Ä¢ Free accommodation and board at each hotel where performances take place, including meals in the main restaurant and beverages
 ‚Ä¢ Accident, pension, and social insurance coverage included
 ‚Ä¢ ‚Ç¨300 travel bonus reimbursed with the final salary for six-month contracts
 ‚Ä¢ Free airport transfer upon arrival in Greece
 ‚Ä¢ Free internet and laundry services
 ‚Ä¢ Work uniforms and costumes provided
 ‚Ä¢ Company car available for work-related purposes
 ‚Ä¢ Additional performance bonus available at the end of the contract
 ‚Ä¢ Potential for career growth within the company and opportunities for contract renewal
 ‚Ä¢ An exceptional opportunity to gain professional and cultural experience under the Greek sun ‚òÄ

üé• Watch our show productions:
https://youtu.be/9PdbLO‚ÄìGX4?si=W8fKURLEWPjE9bCG

üì©Apply Now for Online Auditions! Make Summer 2026 unforgettable ‚Äî send your CV to: adriano@palmera-agency.com

üé¨** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes: WORLDWIDE CASTING CALL **üáµüá≠

We are urgently seeking **experienced male actors (ages 31-49)** for the upcoming project, **"Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes"**! Filming will take place in the **Philippines**.

We are specifically targeting actors who hold **German, British, Czech, or American** citizenship/nationality.

**Project & Role Details**

* **Project Title:** Bad at Hellos Worse at Goodbyes
* **IMDb Link:** [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt38781319/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0_tt_8_nm_0_in_0_q_bad%2520at%2520hellos](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt38781319/?ref_=nv_sr_srsg_0_tt_8_nm_0_in_0_q_bad%2520at%2520hellos)
* **Filming Location:** **Philippines** (Applicants must be willing and able to travel and work in the Philippines).
* **Compensation:** **$5,000 - $7,000 USD**, based on professional credits and experience.
* **Filming dates: **February 2026 - April 2026

**Mandatory Requirements**

* **Gender/Age:** Male, strictly **31 to 49 years old**.
* **Nationality:** Must be a citizen of **Germany, the United Kingdom, the Czech Republic, or the United States**.
* **Professional Profile:** Must have an established **IMDb Profile** with verifiable credits.
* **Social Media:** Must have a minimum of **5,000+ followers** across primary social media platform(s).

**Submission Instructions**

To be considered, please email your full submission package to:

üìß **[badathellosworseatgoodbyes@gmail.com](mailto:badathellosworseatgoodbyes@gmail.com)**

**Subject Line MUST BE:** **"CASTING SUBMISSION: MALE [YOUR AGE] - [NATIONALITY] - [YOUR NAME]"**

**Your submission package must include:**
* Professional Headshot(s) and Acting Resume/CV (attached).
* A link to your Acting Reel or recent work samples.
* A direct link to your verifiable **IMDb Profile**.
* Link(s) to your main Social Media profile(s), clearly stating your current follower count.
* Your current City and Country of residence (and where you currently hold citizenship).

üö®** DEADLINE FOR SUBMISSIONS**

All materials must be received no later than **November 26th or 27th, 2025**.

*Only selected candidates meeting ****ALL**** mandatory requirements will be contacted for auditions.*
